OL,4,Cvictim if she called police
OL,6,F"She must have been absolutely
OL,7,Fterrified of this evil man and I want
OL,8,Fto commend her bravery and courage in
OL,9,Fcoming forward to tell us all the
OL,10,Fcrimes he had subjected her to."
OL,12,FMacalla was charged with rape,
OL,13,Fharassment, criminal damage, sending
OL,14,Fthreatening messages, possession of
OL,15,Fdrugs and driving while disqualified.
OL,17,FHe admitted all the offences except
OL,18,Frape and harassment but was convicted
OL,19,Fof those by a jury at Sheffield Crown
OL,20,FCourt.
